{"name": "os-toolkit", "metadata": {"name": "os-toolkit", "version": "0.1.2", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pandas", "py-string-tool", "python-wizard"], "summary": "package build on top of os and add more convient functionality", "upload_time": 1718438310}, "documentation": [""], "modules": [{"name": "os_toolkit.test01", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "os_toolkit.sandbox1_ost", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "os_toolkit.sandbox1_ost.os_add_extension", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ori_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "added_extension", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "inplace", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Add an extension to file paths.\n\nThis function appends a specified extension to file paths. The function can modify the original file paths or return new file paths with the added extension.\n\n# Parameters\n\nori_path\n\n: The original file path or a list of file paths to which the extension will be added.\n\nadded_extension\n\n: The extension to be added to the file path(s). The extension can be provided with or without the leading dot (e.g., '.txt' or 'txt').\n\ninplace\n\n: If True, the function modifies the original file path(s). If False, the function returns new file path(s) with the added extension.\n\n# Returns\n\nstr or list of str\n\n: If `inplace` is True, returns the modified original file path or list of file paths.\n  If `inplace` is False, returns a new file path or list of file paths with the added extension.\n  If a single file path is provided and `inplace` is False, returns a single modified file path.\n\n# Examples\n\nAdd an extension to a single file path and modify the original path:\n\n```pycon\n>>> os_add_extension('example', 'txt')\n'example.txt'\n```\n\nAdd an extension to a list of file paths and return new paths:\n\n```pycon\n>>> os_add_extension(['file1', 'file2'], '.md', inplace=False)\n['file1.md', 'file2.md']\n```\n"]}, {"name": "os_toolkit.sandbox1_ost.create_folders", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "folder", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "name_list", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "replace", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Sub"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "os_toolkit.cant_use_ost", "documentation": ["the diff between fix_bug vs cant_use is that:", "fix_bug: you can still use some functionality of it, it's that there's some parameter like(alarm path) that still have the problem", "cant_use: the main functionality is not correct, or may not work entirely"], "functions": [{"name": "os_toolkit.cant_use_ost.filesize_in_folder", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "folder_path", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "pd.DataFrame", "xref": {"fqname": "pandas.DataFrame", "project": "pandas"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"na